FAQ
See our complete list of FAQs for this upcoming MLS Season here.

  • When does the 2024 MLS season start?

    MLS announced that the 2024 Regular Season will kick off earlier than ever before with Opening Weekend scheduled to start on February 21, 2024 and conclude on October 19, 2024. Each team will play 34 regular season matches 17 at home and 17 away. The All-Star Game is scheduled for July 17, 2024, at the Columbus Crews Lower.com Field in Columbus Ohio. Following the regular season, the MLS Playoffs will begin in October and will culminate with the 2024 MLS Cup.

  • How much do MLS tickets cost?

    Tickets are priced by the team and fluctuate by game. According to Ticketmaster data, the price of MLS tickets cost between $45 and $50, on average. Prices vary on secondary and resale marketplaces.

  • How do I buy MLS tickets?

    Tickets for the 2024 MLS season are available now. Ticketmaster is your trusted source to find tickets guaranteed to get you in on game day including verified resale tickets. Digital tickets are instantly delivered to your phone, so you can shop for and buy them right up until the game starts.

  • When do MLS tickets go on sale?

    Fans can now purchase tickets to cheer on their favorite team during the 2024 MLS season. Ticketmaster has a wide selection of MLS tickets available, including verified resale tickets. Whether youre looking for tickets to tomorrows game, next weeks game or a game happening next month, you can score them today at Ticketmaster.

  • Do MLS season tickets include playoffs?

    While season ticket plans dont typically include playoff tickets, most teams give their season ticket holders the opportunity to purchase their season seats for all playoff home games as theyre announced. Each MLS teams season ticket holder program is different, so for more information on how season tickets work, and to become a season ticket member, visit your favorite MLS teams official website.

  • When do MLS Cup tickets go on sale?

    Tickets to the 2024 MLS Cup will likely go on sale the week leading up to the game. Keep checking Ticketmaster as the playoffs come to an end and the matchup is set as tickets will become available. MLS Cup tickets are usually made available first to season ticket holders and then released to the general public.

  • What is the MLS Ticket Exchange?

    The MLS Ticket Exchange is Ticketmasters safe and secure marketplace for purchasing tickets to see your favorite MLS team live. You can find standard tickets for select MLS teams, as well as verified resale tickets being sold by other fans. Ticketmaster gives you a safe and convenient way to buy or sell tickets for the 2024 MLS season.

Additional Information About the MLS

Major League Soccer History

Buoyed by interest in soccer following the 1994 World Cup in the United States, and filling the void left in 1984 by the defunct NASL, the inaugural season of Major League Soccer was in 1996, with 10 teams spread across 48 states, from Los Angeles to Tampa Bay.

The league experienced huge growth, going from 10 to 24 teams in the first two decades. After Americas success in the 2002 World Cup, the league adopted international standards for play. As MLS has gotten bigger, many teams have moved to soccer-specific stadiums and with the popularity of MLS, international signings from other leagues is a common occurance nowadays.

In 2022, a new team, Charlotte FC, joined the MLS roster, bringing the total number of MLS teams to 28. The MLS newest and 29th franchise, St. Louis City SC, began play in the 2023 season and the league will expand again in 2025 with the addition of the San Diego FC. The future is bright for Major League Soccer, and Ticketmaster offers you unparalleled access to games.

 

MLS Preseason

After all the off-season moves, its time to get ready for the upcoming season new players, new coaches, and a new swing at glory. Come see your team as they use the preseason as an opportunity to figure out what works, fix what doesnt, and get prepared for the start of the regular season on February 21. Its your first chance to catch your team out on the pitch in person.

 

MLS Regular Season

Now is when the games really matter. From February 21 to October 19, each of the leagues 28 teams play 34 action-packed games. The team with the top regular season record takes home the coveted Supporters Shield, and Ticketmaster is your best bet for grabbing the best seats for the teams and players you wanna see.

The Leagues Cup breaks things up in the middle of the season between July 26 and August 15, as well as the All-Star Game taking place on July 17 in Columbus, OH, and Ticketmaster can get you to that game, too. It features the top MLS soccer stars playing together, pitted against a top international football club from a league abroad.

 

MLS Cup Playoffs

MLS Cup Playoffs are when things really heat up. Its an all-out race to the MLS Cup Final, with the top seven teams from both the Western and Eastern Conference facing off. The top seed in each league gets a 1-week bye. The winner of the MLS Cup Final which takes place November 5 is awarded the coveted MLS Cup. Last year, the Columbus Crew won their third championship at the 2023 MLS Cup, beating LAFC by a score of 2-1. When its time, grab your MLS Playoff Tickets at Ticketmaster and get to the games.

Privacy Preference Center

  • Your Privacy

  • Strictly Necessary Tracking Technologies

  • Functional Tracking Technologies

  • Performance Tracking Technologies

  • Advertising & Targeting Tracking Technologies

Your Privacy

When you visit any website, it may store or retrieve information on your browser, mostly in the form of cookies. This information might be about you, your preferences or your device and is mostly used to make the site work as you expect it to. The information does not usually directly identify you, but it can give you a more personalized web experience. Because we respect your right to privacy, you can choose not to allow some types of cookies. Click on the different category headings to find out more and change our default settings. However, blocking some types of cookies may impact your experience of the site and the services we are able to offer.

Ad Choices: Your online browsing activity may be collected on this site by third party advertisers for cross-site interest-based advertising. Click here to learn more about interest based and behavioral advertising.

In addition, the Digital Advertising Alliance offers a tool for opting out of the collection of cross-app data on a mobile device for interest-based advertising. To exercise choice for companies participating in this tool, download the Appchoices app here. To learn more about IBA or to opt-out of this type of advertising, go to https://optout.aboutads.info/.

Strictly Necessary Tracking Technologies

Always Active

These Strictly Necessary Tracking Technologies are necessary for the website to function and cannot be switched off in our systems. They are usually only set in response to actions made by you which amount to a request for services, such as setting your privacy preferences, logging in or filling in forms.    You can set your browser to block or alert you about these technologies, but some parts of the site will not then work. These technologies do not store any personally identifiable information.

Functional Tracking Technologies

These Functional Tracking Technologies enable the website to provide enhanced functionality and personalisation. They may be set by us or by third party providers whose services we have added to our pages.    If you do not allow these technologies then some or all of these services may not function properly.

Performance Tracking Technologies

These Performance Tracking Technologies allow us to count visits and traffic sources so we can measure and improve the performance of our site. They help us to know which pages are the most and least popular and see how visitors move around the site.    All information these technologies collect is aggregated and therefore anonymous. If you do not allow these technologies we will not know when you have visited our site, and will not be able to monitor its performance.

Advertising & Targeting Tracking Technologies

These Advertising and Targeting Tracking Technologies may be set through our site by our advertising partners. They may be used by those companies to build a profile of your interests and show you relevant adverts on other sites.    They do not store directly personal information, but are based on uniquely identifying your browser and internet device. If you do not allow these technologies, you will experience less targeted advertising.
